<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:4pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:0.50em; margin-right:0.20em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>MBIA Insurance Liquidity</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:4pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Ensuring that sufficient liquidity exists for any claim payments due is critical to protecting MBIA Insurance, its policyholders
and creditors</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="5"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:4pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:0.50em; margin-right:0.20em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Expense Management</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:4pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Focusing on expense management ensures that MBIA is efficient in allocating resources where needed while complying with capital and
liquidity requirements</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="5"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:4pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:0.50em; margin-right:0.20em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>People Management</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:4pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In a challenging environment, remaining focused on supporting, developing and retaining high potential employees and improving
workforce diversity is important to ensure our ability to execute our other goals</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Compensation Practices </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">MBIA has adopted a number of policies and practices relating to compensation which we believe are in the best interests of our shareholders. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="49%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="49%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:3pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;Best Practices and policies that we follow</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:3pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Practices that we do not follow</B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="5"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Deliver the
majority of target compensation in the form of variable pay</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Tie variable pay to successful performance in areas of strategic significance</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Assess performance both quantitatively and qualitatively to ensure
appropriate outcomes</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Cap the cash annual incentive opportunity</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Use
equity vehicles, and established stock ownership guidelines and stock retention requirements beyond retirement, to directly align NEO interests with those of shareholders</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Phase
the vesting of equity awards over a five year period</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Operate a clawback policy</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Apply double-trigger for change in control payments</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Prohibit short sales, hedging or pledging of our stock</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.50em; margin-right:0.20em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Engage
an external independent advisor</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Provide guaranteed bonuses</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Encourage excessive
risk</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Provide
excessive perquisites</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Make decisions solely based on market data</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Offer employment
contracts</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8201;Grant
back-dated or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">make-up</FONT> incentive awards</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>16 </B></FONT></P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I><A NAME="tx841074_102"></A>Compensation Approach </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The MBIA executive compensation program comprises three core elements: a base salary, annual cash incentive opportunity and long-term incentive opportunity,
delivered in the form of MBIA stock. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The majority of compensation for our CEO and other NEOs is delivered in the form of performance-based compensation,
the weighting of which has increased in recent years based on shareholder feedback. In 2019, 62% of the CEO&#146;s target compensation and 59% of the other NEOs&#146; respective target compensation (on average) was performance-based. In February
2020 the Committee approved no changes in target total compensation for the CEO and other NEOs in respect of 2020. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g841074g82u09.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><I>Base salary reflects the salary set in respect of the relevant year; annual incentive reflects the target value of the award
in respect of the year, paid within 2 months thereafter; time and performance-based long-term incentives reflect the target value of the award in respect of the year, granted within 2.5 months thereafter. CEO data reflects Mr.&nbsp;Fallon, and NEO
data is the average for the other NEOs. </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In addition to the compensation outlined below, MBIA&#146;s executives receive the same benefits as our
general employee population. This includes participation in healthcare benefits, where MBIA shares in the cost of employee health insurance coverage; supplemental disability insurance; and contributions to defined contribution retirement programs
based on a stated percentage of the employee&#146;s compensation. No perquisites are paid to current NEOs. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>17 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>

element has been made for 2020: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Performance Measures</I></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Base Salary</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">To compensate executives competitively for their roles at
MBIA</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Fixed pay</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;Informed by reference to peer
group median and adjusted for, among other variables, tenure, knowledge, ability and experience</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Level also takes account of scope of role</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Reviewed
annually</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Not applicable</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Annual Incentive Award</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">To drive performance against annual strategic goals and reward appropriately</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Variable pay delivered in
cash</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Value
determined based on performance against <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-defined</FONT> objectives</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Target values set with reference to peer group median</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Actual bonus can range from
0% to 200% of target</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Based on performance against the
corporate scorecard of quantifiable objectives</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Performance goals based on MBIA&#146;s three-year tactical and strategic objectives</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="5"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Long-Term Incentive<BR>Compensation</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;<FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Performance-Based Shares</I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">To drive performance against critical strategic imperatives that create
sustainable long-term shareholder value, align senior leader interests with shareholders and reward appropriately</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Variable pay delivered, if at all, in
equity</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Accounts
for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-thirds</FONT> of the total long-term compensation</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Target values informed by reference to peer group median</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Target award grant date
value of 100% of base salary (117% for CEO)</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Actual payout can range from 0% to 200% of target award</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Earned shares vest in equal
installments on the third, fourth and fifth anniversaries of the date of grant</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Earned shares vest subject to continued employment and performance</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Assessed against <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> performance measures</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Vesting of 2018 and 2019 awards made in early 2019 and 2020, respectively, are based solely on total shareholder return</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Performance is assessed at
the end of the three-year performance period (December&nbsp;31, 2021 for the March 2019 awards)</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Performance shares will be forfeited if minimum targets are not met; for instance if total
shareholder return is negative over the performance period</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Time-Based Shares</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">To provide a focus on sustainable long-term shareholder value creation, align senior leader interests with shareholders, reward
appropriately and retain senior leaders</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Variable pay delivered in
equity</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Accounts
for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> of the total long-term compensation</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Target values informed by reference to peer group median</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Target award grant date
value of 50% of base salary (58% for CEO)</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Shares vest in equal installments on the third, fourth and fifth anniversaries of date of grant
(annual grants)</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Awards vest subject to continued employment</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Continued employment (condition for vesting)</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>18 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="tx841074_103"></A>Compensation Governance </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">There are a number of factors that come together to ensure proper governance of MBIA&#146;s compensation programs. This section will look at these in turn,
discussing the importance and function of each. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>Compensation Oversight</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The Compensation and Governance Committee comprises MBIA&#146;s five independent outside directors, each of whom was recruited to join MBIA on account of their
expertise and seniority in a substantive area (such as banking, accounting and/or asset management) of relevance to MBIA&#146;s core strategic agenda. During 2019, the Committee met five times in regular session and has overall responsibility for
overseeing MBIA&#146;s compensation programs, approving as a Committee and providing input and recommendations to the Board regarding our NEOs&#146; compensation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The Committee receives information and support from management, and expert guidance from an independent committee advisor, both of which impact the ultimate recommendations the Committee makes to the Board.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g841074g11c31.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Additional information on the Committee can be found on page&nbsp;3 in the &#147;Board of Directors corporate governance
section&#148;. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>Use of an Independent Advisor</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Since 2009, the Committee has retained Willis Towers Watson as an advisor to provide independent advice on a range of compensation issues. This primarily involves assisting in analyzing the competitiveness of NEO
and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director compensation, reviewing incentive design, periodically assisting in reviewing the competitive peer group and other activities as directed by the Committee. The Committee uses Willis
Towers Watson&#146;s advice and insight to inform the eventual decision making process. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In assessing Willis Towers Watson&#146;s independence, the
Committee considered the six independence factors for compensation consultants listed in the NYSE listing requirements and determined that Willis Towers Watson did not have a conflict of interest. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Shareholder Engagement</I></B> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">MBIA takes shareholder
outreach and feedback seriously, and senior management interacts regularly with our shareholders. Additionally, in recent years the Chair of the Committee has participated directly in shareholder engagement to ensure we broadly receive direct and
constructive feedback to inform our thinking on NEO compensation and other issues of importance to shareholders. This feedback has had a meaningful impact on both our compensation philosophy and program design. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>19 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>

<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In 2019, led by the Chair of the Committee, our CEO, and our Head of Investor Relations, we invited over 65% of our shareholders to speak with us,
and engaged with shareholders representing in excess of 40% of our outstanding shares at March&nbsp;7, 2019, either in person or by phone.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; line-height:13.0pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">These calls and meetings provided an open forum to discuss those topics which were of most significance to our shareholders, which included but
was not limited to executive compensation. The feedback received regarding our executive compensation program has been uniformly positive. Consequently, the Committee and the Board of Directors have not made any material structural</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><U>2019 Shareholder Engagement</U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:5px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Engaged with shareholders accounting for over 40% of outstanding shares</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:5px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Reviewed Glass Lewis and
ISS reports</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:5px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; margin-right:0.60em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Feedback confirmed shareholder satisfaction with our executive compensation
program</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:5px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">program changes for 2020. There is no intention to make any <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">off-cycle</FONT> awards, which was an
area of concern identified by the proxy advisors who have been engaged by some of our shareholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Looking to the future, MBIA is committed to
continuing to maintain ongoing dialogue with our major shareholders to ensure we remain fully aware of shareholder expectations and concerns. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>The Annual Process</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The Committee is
responsible for reviewing the design, levels and outcomes under MBIA&#146;s NEO compensation program, along with associated feedback from shareholders. It typically meets five times per year to execute upon the various procedural steps outlined
below. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>Managing Compensation-Related Risks</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Risk is a central part of MBIA&#146;s business, and appropriately managing that risk is critical to our success. Our approach to risk management is evident in the
very core of our business. Our values embrace integrity, through our Standard of Conduct, and underscore our commitment to performance excellence. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The
Committee&#146;s role relative to risk mitigation is to design and review our compensation programs to ensure that they do not encourage unnecessary, inappropriate or excessive risk-taking. The Committee&#146;s role spans the structure of the
programs themselves, including the weighting of the relative components of compensation, along with the targets attached to variable compensation opportunities. Each year, the Committee assesses MBIA&#146;s compensation policies and practices to
evaluate whether they create risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on MBIA. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In conducting this assessment the Committee
considered a range of areas, including: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The performance measures, and their relative balance, used within our incentive plans; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The attributes of MBIA&#146;s compensation practices, such as pay mix and the range of potential minimum to maximum payouts; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The design of MBIA&#146;s broader compensation policies. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Based on its assessment for 2019, the Committee concluded that MBIA&#146;s compensation policies and practices do not create incentives to take risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on
MBIA, while providing adequate incentives to build sustainable long-term shareholder value. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">There are a number of features of our executive compensation
programs that demonstrate our strong commitment to appropriately mitigating compensation-related risk which are considered as part of this assessment, and we will look at each of these in turn. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Use of Discretion and Judgment.</I></B> To discourage imprudent risk taking by our NEOs, when assessing outcomes under the annual incentive plan, the
Committee takes account of performance against the established Company objectives, as well as a macro level view of performance and behaviors. This enables the Committee to assess not only MBIA&#146;s accomplishments, but also how these
accomplishments were achieved. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">If needed, the Committee can use its discretion to adjust, up or down, annual incentive awards to take into account any
unanticipated or extraordinary events, or broader performance that did not align with expectations or poor risk management. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">At its meeting in February
2020, the Committee did not exercise discretion to adjust the outcome of the objective application of the Company&#146;s 2019 scorecard to determine NEO annual incentive awards. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>21 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Clawback.</I></B> In February 2013, MBIA adopted a Clawback Policy which covers all compensation paid or
awarded. The policy is intended to promote ethical behavior and accountability with respect to the accuracy of financial reporting. The following table summarizes the key features of the policy: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;All executives with the
title &#145;Managing Director&#146; or above, at the time of a restatement or any time during the three-year period preceding the restatement</FONT></P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;A material restatement of our GAAP financial statements which means that
any compensation paid to a Covered Executive would have been lower</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">

equity</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Determining the value of a clawback</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Amount determined at the
Committee&#146;s discretion</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

that would have been paid or granted under the restated financial statements</FONT></P></TD></TR>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">This policy will be reviewed from time to time, to consider potential changes that may reflect evolving best practices, regulation,
MBIA&#146;s circumstances, or other relevant factors. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>22 </B></FONT></P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Stock Ownership Guidelines.</I></B> MBIA has implemented stock ownership guidelines which were adopted to
align senior management&#146;s interests with those of our shareholders. Under these guidelines, certain senior employees are expected to own MBIA stock worth a value equal to a multiple of their base salary. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="75%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="4" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cceeff" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:6pt ;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Role</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:6pt ;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>&nbsp;<BR></I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:6pt ;" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Ownership&nbsp;Guideline<BR>(Multiple&nbsp;of&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Salary)</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="padding-bottom:6pt ;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I><BR>&nbsp;</I></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="4" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Chief Executive Officer</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="right" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">7x</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cceeff" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Chief Financial Officer and other NEOs</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">3x</FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">As of December&nbsp;31, 2019, the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer have already exceeded their ownership
guidelines, with other NEOs making progress toward their guidelines in light of their respective appointment dates. In assessing achievement, stock owned directly and any stock held in retirement plans will be counted. Interests such as the value of
unvested restricted stock or unvested stock options are not counted. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Stock Holding Periods.</I></B> Once an NEO has achieved his or her ownership
guideline, they are permitted to divest 25% of any excess above the guidelines during any <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">12-month</FONT> period while the individual is still employed. Individuals are also permitted to sell stock for the purpose of
settling taxes on long-term incentive awards. Notably, no current NEO has ever sold any MBIA stock other than as an offset to the taxes incurred when shares vested. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Upon retirement, individuals are permitted to sell <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> of his or her holdings immediately, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> a year after termination
and the final third two years after termination. This does not preclude any individual electing to maintain his or her holdings for a longer period of time. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Company Policies Prohibit Hedging and/or Pledging of Company Stock.</I></B> MBIA maintains rigorous anti-hedging and anti-pledging of shares policies. Specifically, MBIA&#146;s Insider Trading Policy
prohibits Directors, officers and employees from (i)&nbsp;engaging in hedging transactions, (ii)&nbsp;pledging MBIA securities as a collateral, or (iii)&nbsp;holding MBIA securities in a margin account, without the prior approval of such
transactions by the MBIA Legal Department. The MBIA Legal Department has not been requested to approve any such transactions, and has not done so, in over ten years. The Policy also prohibits directors, officers and employees from engaging in short
sales or transactions involving puts, calls and other types of options in MBIA&#146;s securities, including equity swaps and similar derivative transactions. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>Compensation Peer Group</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Another integral part of our compensation governance is the
Committee&#146;s review of MBIA&#146;s compensation programs relative to what its peers are doing in the market. When reviewing our compensation programs, while keeping a keen focus on what is in MBIA&#146;s and shareholders&#146; best interests,
the Committee&#146;s understanding of market practices to assess the competitiveness and appropriateness of compensation is an important consideration as well. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><U>Principles for identifying compensation peers</U></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Operate in similar or
comparable industry segments: Property and Casualty Insurance, Reinsurance</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Subject to similar legal or regulatory environments</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Comparable in size and scope</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Competitor for
talent</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">One of the challenges for MBIA when establishing its peer group is the limited number of directly comparable organizations. Part of the Committee&#146;s overall review of the Company&#146;s
executive compensation program over the past several years included developing underlying principles for identifying peers (at left), and updating the parameters, which, in 2017, resulted in 12 companies being removed from the previous peer group
and 15 companies being added. It is not necessarily the case that all the factors apply to every peer company. Ultimately, the Committee has applied judgement in arriving at the composition of the current group, which currently consists of 19
companies. This peer group has not changed from last year.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

Insurance Corporation</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"> </SUP></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8201;&#8201;RLI Corp.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8201;&#8201;Third Point Reinsurance</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8201;&#8201;United Insurance Holdings</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8201;&#8201;Universal Insurance
Holdings</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8201;&#8201;White

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">(1)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Subsequent to the Committee&#146;s NEO and Director market compensation review in 2019, EMC Insurance Group went private and will not be included in our
peer group going forward. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">We consider it important to evaluate ourselves against a robust peer group that is large enough to withstand
potential changes to the composite companies. MBIA is ranked in the top quartile of the peer group from an assets perspective, first quartile of the peer group from a revenue perspective, and second quartile from a market capitalization perspective
at the time of our market compensation review in 2019. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>24 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="tx841074_104"></A>2019 Compensation Decisions and Outcomes </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>An Overview of Performance in 2019</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Like
the several years preceding it, 2019 presented MBIA with significant challenges. The Committee believes that through the efforts of our senior team and broader employee base to address those challenges, they have positioned MBIA to deliver long-term
value for its shareholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">After 2017&#146;s determination to shut down National&#146;s new business efforts and the Company&#146;s subsequent <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">right-sizing</FONT> of the organization, which reduced the annual operating expense run rate by over $25&nbsp;million to less than $75&nbsp;million, the Company is now primarily focused on (i)&nbsp;ensuring that adequate
liquidity exists at the holding company to satisfy all outstanding obligations, (ii)&nbsp;maximizing the economics of National&#146;s existing insured portfolio through effective surveillance and remediation activity, and by managing its investment
portfolio, and (iii)&nbsp;satisfying claims by MBIA Corp. policyholders, pursuing various actions focused on maximizing the collection of recoveries for its senior lending and surplus note holders, and then its preferred stock holders, and reducing
and mitigating potential losses on its insurance exposures. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In 2019, satisfaction of these goals was largely focused on the Company&#146;s efforts to
remediate its troubled Puerto Rico credits. The Company achieved a significant success in this regard in 2019 when it, along with other parties, closed on a series of transactions emanating from the 2018 comprehensive settlement with the Oversight
Board responsible for managing Puerto Rico&#146;s bankruptcy-like (Title III of PROMESA) restructuring processes, concerning the debt of COFINA. After the Court overseeing the Title III process approved the settlement in February 2019 and entered an
order confirming the Third Amended Title III Plan of Adjustment for COFINA, National exercised its rights to sell the new uninsured bonds that had been placed into National Custodial Trusts per the Plan of Adjustment, and subsequently, through a
final voluntary payment that fulfilled its insurance obligations in full, reduced to zero its COFINA gross par outstanding, gross par outstanding plus capital appreciation bonds accreted interest, and debt service outstanding. Additionally, in
September of 2019, National agreed to join the restructuring support agreement, as amended (&#147;RSA&#148;), with the Puerto Rico Electric Power Authority (&#147;PREPA&#148;), and other parties including Puerto Rico and the Oversight Board. The
restructuring transaction described in the RSA is intended to, among other things, provide a framework for the consensual resolution of the treatment of National&#146;s insured PREPA revenue bonds in PREPA&#146;s recovery plan. The RSA remains
subject to conditions, satisfaction of which cannot be assured. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">When these developments and others, including surpassing our target for Adjusted Book
Value, a metric which we consider a measure of fundamental Company value, and achieving several liquidity goals for the holding company and at MBIA Insurance, were measured against the Company&#146;s annual performance scorecard, as discussed
further below, performance for the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2019 resulted in annual incentive awards at 107% of target. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The compensation of our
NEOs in 2019 is explained in the following sections and in the Summary Compensation Table that follows. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>Base Salary</I></B><B>
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Base salaries are generally set based on the job content of each position, informed by salary data for comparable positions within our compensation
peer group. From time to time, adjustments are also made based on the executive&#146;s experience, performance and potential. The Committee generally targets base salaries for the NEOs around the market median for executives in similar positions
within the compensation peer group. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>25 </B></FONT></P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>2019 Annual Incentive</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The annual incentive is a performance bonus, paid in cash, which is designed to compensate NEOs for progress against MBIA&#146;s shorter-term tactical and strategic objectives. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B></B><B><I>Annual Incentive Awards for 2019 Performance</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The 2019 annual incentive for NEOs, as well as other associates at MBIA more broadly, is based on a scorecard of performance in four key areas, discussed in detail below: performance in our two operating
subsidiaries, National (30% of total score) and MBIA Insurance (15%); performance at the corporate holding company level (10%); and enterprise-wide performance (45%). The objectives in each of these areas, along with the underlying performance
targets, align to MBIA&#146;s shorter-term tactical and strategic plan, providing direct alignment to our business strategy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The table below reflects
the outcome for the scorecard for 2019, including the four areas and underlying performance objectives. Each area and goal had an associated weighting, as noted, which was used to determine the overall score under the plan, and the chart below
reflects the weight and performance level assigned to each goal. The goals have been identified as strategic priorities, and are appropriate for inclusion in the annual incentive plan as they focus on areas that are of critical importance to the
value proposition of shareholders, and on which senior leaders can take action today. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>2019 Annual Incentive Scorecard </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="66%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="0%"></TD>
<TD nowrap style="width:10pt"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD nowrap style="width:10pt"></TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Excluding People Management, which was achieved at expectations, performance highlights in each of the four areas
were as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="5" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:2pt ;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>National</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:2pt ;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>MBIA Insurance Corporation</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Scoring for portfolio management and remediation of troubled credits in National&#146;s
portfolio is largely focused on outcomes related to its Puerto Rico credits. Outcomes are established for each of the individual credits for which the Company has material exposure; PREPA, COFINA, General Obligation and HTA, as well as for
collective general developments. A majority of final outcomes remain to be determined</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;As discussed earlier in this CD&amp;A, the Company achieved success in 2019 by eliminating its
COFINA exposure, which had accounted for approximately 52% of total debt service to Puerto Rico. Progress against PREPA goals fell below target, notwithstanding that National joined the RSA as discussed. Progress against General Obligation and HTA
goals was not subject to evaluation by year end in light of the status of those restructuring negotiations in the Title III proceedings, and weight for these categories were reassigned. Progress against general goals for Puerto Rico remediation were
judged at below target</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Significant liquidity initiatives executed during the year, enabling a significant prepay of
senior creditor notes and a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">year-end</FONT> liquidity balance that still materially exceeded target</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Completed a refinance of a senior credit facility at a lower rate and at a lower principal
balance, compared to the original facility</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Failed to achieve targeted goals concerning recovery on Zohar credit payments, for which efforts
will continue in 2020</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Active in executing remediation strategies for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-Zohar</FONT>
exposures</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="5" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:2pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Corporate Segment</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="padding-bottom:2pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>Enterprise Objectives</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Liquidity initiatives, including the strategic call of debt, rebalancing of our swap portfolio, and receipt of dividends, led to a position of significant excess to target, enhancing
Company ability to satisfy obligations during the strategic plan period</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;The Company&#146;s Adjusted Book Value per share as of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">year-end</FONT> 2019 was $29.38, versus $27.38 as of
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">year-end</FONT> 2018, significantly exceeding the target of $26.68 approved by the Board in February 2019. Target is set with an expectation of a reduction in year-over-year ABV, given the Company&#146;s decision to
cease pursuing new business. Any significant losses at National will tend to reduce ABV versus target. In 2019, strategic repurchase of shares, coupled with unplanned gains on the sale of PREPA and COFINA bonds at National, offset losses and drove
the positive outcome</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;ABV is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> measure discussed in the
Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the fiscal year ended December&nbsp;31, 2019; the Company views changes to this measure as an important indicator of financial performance</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Regarding Expense
Management, the Company kept ordinary course operating expenses at a level that would have yielded a target level performance; however, the Company incurred significant legal expenses in bringing a new litigation related to losses it suffered on its
Puerto Rico credits. While the Company believes the litigation may yield significant value to shareholders, the expenses incurred were not part of the original plan and pushed the score for this measure to zero</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>27 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In 2019, target bonus opportunities for the NEOs were as follows. The maximum bonus opportunity is capped at <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-times</FONT> the target opportunity. Company performance resulted in a final annual incentive outcome of 107% of target, which equated to the following annual incentive awards in respect of 2019 performance for our
NEOs: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>2019 Long-Term Incentive Awards </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">In response to
feedback from our shareholders, since March 2017 long-term incentive awards to NEOs are made in the form of a combination of performance-based and time-based share awards. This combination provides immediate alignment to shareholder value creation
and long-term shareholder interests, as well as a focus on the strategic drivers of MBIA&#146;s long-term performance. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">For 2019, our NEOs&#146;
long-term incentive awards feature the same ratio of performance-based to time-based shares as has been applied since 2017, as shown below. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:0px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g841074g30j30.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Any shares that are earned will vest in equal installments on the third, fourth, and fifth anniversary of the grant date:
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The same vesting approach will apply to awards made in March 2020. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>2019 Performance-Based Share Awards. </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Performance-based share awards are made in the form of MBIA
equity. Long-term incentive awards made in March 2019 (for the 2018 performance year) to each of the NEOs, comprised a combination of performance-based shares and time-based </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>28 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">
shares. The annual target grant date value of the long-term incentive awards for our CEO was 175% of base salary and, for our other NEOs, 150% of base salary, with
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-thirds</FONT> of the award being in the form of performance-based shares and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> in the form of time-based shares. This mix continues to align NEOs with delivering
sustainable shareholder value creation, while linking pay to MBIA performance. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Vesting of the performance-based shares is based on performance against
company value, which provides direct alignment with the shareholder experience of value creation, assessed via absolute total shareholder return (TSR) over a three year period ending on December&nbsp;31, 2021. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The table below sets out the associated performance requirements for TSR for awards made in March 2019, along with the corresponding percentage of shares that can
be earned, ranging from 0% to 200% of the target award. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="line-height:14.0pt"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">%&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">TSR is the change in the value of the common stock over the three year period, taking into account both stock price appreciation and
the payment of dividends if applicable. TSR will be calculated on a compound annualized basis over the three year period. The beginning stock price is the closing share price as of December&nbsp;31, 2018. The ending stock price will be the average
stock price over the 60 trading days preceding and including the last day of the performance period. Straight-line interpolation will apply to performance levels between the TSR values. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The following performance-based share awards were made with these conditions to NEOs in March 2019: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>Pay for performance</I></B><B><I></I></B><B><I>&nbsp;&#150; Lapse of 2017 Performance Shares</I></B>. As part of its pay for
performance practices, the Company made restricted stock awards to Messrs. Fallon and McKiernan in March 2017. The vesting of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> of the awards was time-based, and vesting of the other <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-thirds</FONT> was performance-based. The grant provided for the forfeiture of the performance-based restricted stock at the end of the three-year performance period (December 31, 2016 through December&nbsp;31, 2019) if
the company&#146;s ABV, Leverage and Stock Price did not exceed the performance threshold established </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B>29 </B></FONT></P>

</DIV></Center>

at grant for each respective metric. As of December&nbsp;31, 2019, the end of the three-year performance period, all of the performance-based restricted shares were forfeited because the
performance threshold for each metric was not met. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The table below shows&nbsp;the number and value of performance-based shares awarded on the grant

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">0</FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">0</FONT></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2"><B><I>2020 Long-Term Incentive Awards </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">Long-term incentive awards made to each of the NEOs in early 2020 (for the 2019 performance year), again comprised a combination of performance-based shares and time-based shares. The annual target grant date value
of the long-term incentive awards for our CEO is 175% of base salary and, for our other NEOs, 150% of base salary, in all cases with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-thirds</FONT> of the award being in the form of performance-based shares and <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> in the form of time-based shares. This mix continues to align NEOs with delivering sustainable shareholder value creation, while linking pay to MBIA performance. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The vesting of the March 2020 performance-based share awards will be contingent on TSR over the three years ending on December&nbsp;31, 2022. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="2">The table below sets out the associated performance requirements for stock price and TSR for awards made in 2020, along with the corresponding percentage of shares
that can be earned, ranging from 0% to 200% of the target award. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
